sentences.english: The world largest arthropod is the Japanese Spider Crab.
sentences.chinese: 世界上最大的節肢動物是日本蜘蛛蟹。

sentences.english: Crayfish belong to a group of animals called Crustaceans and are part of the phylum Arthropoda.
sentences.chinese: 所有的節肢動物都有堅硬的外殼起到骨骼的作用。

sentences.english: A segment of the limb of an arthropod.
sentences.chinese: 節肢動物中一類包括水黽。

sentences.english: How many legs do centipedes and millipedes have?
sentences.chinese: 蜈蚣和倍足綱節肢動物有多少條腿？

sentences.english: It may be mechanically transmitted by arthropods .
sentences.chinese: 它可以通過節肢動物機械地傳播。

sentences.english: Butterflies and shrimps and other animals with jointedlegs belong to Arthropoda.
sentences.chinese: 蝴蝶和蝦以及其他長有節足的動物屬於節肢動物門。

sentences.english: The arthropod community structure and diversity influenced by the forest type.
sentences.chinese: 林分類型對節肢動物羣落結構及多樣性的影響。

sentences.english: The Japanese Spider Crab is the World's Largest Crustacean and Arthropod.
sentences.chinese: 日本蜘蛛蟹，是世界上最大的甲殼動物和節肢動物。

sentences.english: Permethrin repels and kills mosquitoes as well as ticks and other arthropods.
sentences.chinese: 菊酯排斥和殺死蚊子以及蜱和其他節肢動物。

sentences.english: Molting can be observed in all arthropods.
sentences.chinese: 所有的節肢動物都可以觀察到蛻皮。
